## Save Format
Dogeminer 2 saves data very differently to it's predecessor. In [Dogeminer 1](https://dogeminer.se) ([Modified here!](https://realben9.github.io/dm1sc)), a save created at the beginning of the game would look something like ``, which is `{"animate":true,"bganim":true,"bonuscoins":0,"ceffects":true,"clicks":0,"level1":{"alltimecoins":0,"basecost":1000000,"bases":0,"basestrength":5000,"baseupslevel":0,"clickstrength":1,"clickupslevel":0,"coins":0,"extrastrength":1,"extraupslevel":0,"kennelcost":400,"kennels":0,"kennelstrength":3.5,"kennelsupslevel":0,"kittencost":6000,"kittens":0,"kittenstrength":13,"kittensupslevel":0,"rigcost":999999999,"rigs":0,"rigstrength":549215,"rigupslevel":0,"rocketcost":100000,"rockets":0,"rocketstrength":109,"rocketupslevel":0,"shibecost":10,"shibes":0,"shibestrength":0.25,"shibeupslevel":0},"level2":{"alltimecoins":0,"basecost":1000000,"bases":0,"basestrength":5000,"baseupslevel":0,"clickstrength":1,"clickupslevel":0,"coins":0,"extrastrength":1,"extraupslevel":0,"kennelcost":400,"kennels":0,"kennelstrength":3.5,"kennelsupslevel":0,"kittencost":6000,"kittens":0,"kittenstrength":13,"kittensupslevel":0,"rigcost":999999999,"rigs":0,"rigstrength":549215,"rigupslevel":0,"rocketcost":100000,"rockets":0,"rocketstrength":109,"rocketupslevel":0,"shibecost":10,"shibes":0,"shibestrength":0.25,"shibeupslevel":0},"level3":{"alltimecoins":0,"basecost":1000000,"bases":0,"basestrength":5000,"baseupslevel":0,"clickstrength":1,"clickupslevel":0,"coins":0,"extrastrength":1,"extraupslevel":0,"kennelcost":400,"kennels":0,"kennelstrength":3.5,"kennelsupslevel":0,"kittencost":6000,"kittens":0,"kittenstrength":13,"kittensupslevel":0,"rigcost":999999999,"rigs":0,"rigstrength":549215,"rigupslevel":0,"rocketcost":100000,"rockets":0,"rocketstrength":109,"rocketupslevel":0,"shibecost":10,"shibes":0,"shibestrength":0.25,"shibeupslevel":0},"level":1,"maxlevel":1,"music":true,"sounds2":true,"sounds":true,"timeplayed":0,"version":3}` encoded in Base64 format.

*(Base64 can be en/decoded in the console by using `atob()` to decode & `btoa()` to encode.)*

Dogeminer 2 immediately does 2 things differently. The first (& much more noticable) is that a manual save results in a `DOGE` file being downloaded. Next, it adds a layer by compressing the data with LZ, *then* encoding in Base64. In fact, the filetype downloaded prior to v2.8 was `LZ` "due to the name of the compression library". (Taken from the [v2.8 blog](https://blog.dogeminer2.com/Patch-Notes-2.8).)
